article.description: — Fardaws Aimaq had 24 points and 10 rebounds and Utah Valley scored the final eight points to beat Sam Houston 57-54 on Saturday.
article.headline: Aimaq, Harmon rally Utah Valley past Sam Houston 57-54
article.linkText: Aimaq, Harmon rally Utah Valley past Sam Houston 57-54
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Texas -- — Fardaws Aimaq had 24 points and 10 rebounds and Utah Valley scored the final eight points to beat Sam Houston 57-54 on Saturday. Aimaq and Justin Harmon each made a layup and two free throws in the game-ending run for the Wolverines (15-7, 6-4 Western Athletic Conference). Harmon finished with 10 points. Savion Flagg had 12 points for the Bearkats (14-11, 9-3). Sam Houston didn't score after Javion May's bucket gave the Bearkats a 54-49 lead with 3:38 remaining. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ Portions of this story were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
